A community leader and a produce merchant, Pa James Oyebanji Ayinla Arowolo is dead. Aged 120 years. The final burial ceremony takes place on Friday, February 21st 2020. According to a statement by the family, until his death, he was a devoted Christian and an active supporter of gospel activities financially for several decades. The late Pa Arowolo contributed immensely to the development and growth of the Apostolic Church Nigeria in Wakajaiye and Gbongan, Osun State. He was a promoter of peace in the church.